@startuml CAPTheorem

title High-Level Design: CAP Theorem Decision Matrix

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

' Core CAP triangle
component "Consistency (C)\nAll clients read latest write" as C #DDEEFF
component "Availability (A)\nEvery request gets a response" as A #D5E8D4
component "Partition Tolerance (P)\nSystem operates despite network split" as P #F8CECC

C -down- A
A -down- P
P -down- C

note right of P
  In real distributed systems,
  partition is assumed possible.
  So practical choice is often:
  **CP vs AP during partition**.
end note

' Decision flow for interviews
rectangle "Interview Decision Flow" as DF #FFF8E1 {
  rectangle "1) Identify business risk\nWhat must never be wrong?" as d1
  rectangle "2) Assume partition\nInter-AZ/DC link can fail" as d2
  rectangle "3) Choose behavior under split" as d3
  rectangle "CP path\nReject/block uncertain writes\nPreserve correctness" as dcp #DDEEFF
  rectangle "AP path\nServe from available replicas\nReconcile later" as dap #D5E8D4
}

d1 --> d2
d2 --> d3
d3 --> dcp : correctness-critical
d3 --> dap : latency/uptime-critical

' Topic-wise examples
package "Topic-Wise CAP Mapping" #EEF7EE {
  component "CP Leaning\n• Payments\n• Inventory reservation\n• Account balance" as CPX #DDEEFF
  component "AP Leaning\n• Social feed\n• Analytics dashboards\n• Recommendations" as APX #D5E8D4
  component "Mixed Strategy\n• Commands: CP\n• Queries: AP\n(CQRS style)" as MIX #FFF2CC
}

CPX .. dcp
APX .. dap
MIX .. d3

' Practical controls
database "Controls to make tradeoff safe" as CTRL

CPX --> CTRL : quorum, leader writes,\nsync replication
APX --> CTRL : idempotency, retries,\nconflict resolution
MIX --> CTRL : per-endpoint CAP policy,\nobservability, reconciliation jobs

note bottom of CTRL
  Monitor:
  - replication lag
  - stale-read ratio
  - rejected-write rate
  - conflict resolution rate
end note

legend right
  == CAP Interview One-liner ==
  "Under partition, I choose CP or AP
  per workflow based on business risk,
  then apply controls (quorum, idempotency,
  retries, reconciliation)."
endlegend

@enduml

